---
/**
 * context-engineering 0002 · Figure 1 — the hero "selection funnel".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0002-context-selection-and-retrieval.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size,
 * stroke-width, marker-end, …). In an .astro file the SVG is plain HTML, so it
 * renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers ONCE in a shared <defs> block at
 * the top of the document <body> (ids: arw, arwG, arwR, arwM). The MDX has no
 * such shared block, so the markers this figure references (arw, arwM) are
 * inlined into its own <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 322"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A funnel narrows a large corpus to candidates, then ranked, then a selected few packed into the context window."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#b5179e"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="20" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >SELECTION FUNNEL &mdash; many in, a curated few out</text
        >

        <!-- corpus -->
        <rect x="40" y="36" width="560" height="40" rx="6" fill="#efe7f0" stroke="#111110"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Corpus &mdash; every file · doc · record (millions of tokens)</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >far larger than any window</text
        >

        <!-- candidate generation -->
        <rect x="110" y="98" width="420" height="40" rx="6" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="117" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Candidate generation &mdash; cast a wide net</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="131" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >lexical + semantic search · optimize RECALL (don't miss the right one)</text
        >

        <!-- ranking -->
        <rect x="175" y="160" width="290" height="40" rx="6" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="179" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Ranking &mdash; score every candidate</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="193" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >cheap score now · expensive re-rank optional</text
        >

        <!-- selection / packing -->
        <rect x="225" y="222" width="190" height="40" rx="6" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="241" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Selection / packing</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="255" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >fit top-K into budget</text
        >

        <!-- window -->
        <rect
            x="255"
            y="284"
            width="130"
            height="30"
            rx="6"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="303" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Context window</text
        >

        <!-- funnel arrows -->
        <line x1="320" y1="76" x2="320" y2="96" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="320" y1="138" x2="320" y2="158" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="320" y1="200" x2="320" y2="220" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="320" y1="262" x2="320" y2="282" stroke="#b5179e" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Three stages, narrowing each time. <b>Generate</b> casts wide for recall; <b>rank</b> scores;
        <b>select/pack</b> fits the top into the budget — and slips in cheap structural context (signatures,
        not full bodies).<sup><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
